36 ledger record [ISO 22739:2020] - record containing transaction records, hash values of transaction records, or references to transaction records recorded on a distributed ledger.
Note: A reference can be implemented as a cryptographic link.
(27.3) ledger split [ISO 22739:2020]
37 Merkle tree [ISO 22739:2020] - tree data structure in which every leaf node is labelled with the hash value of a data element and every non-leaf node is labelled with the hash value of the labels of its child nodes.
38 Merkle root [ISO 22739:2020] - root node of a Merkle tree.
39 miner [ISO 22739:2020] - DLT node which engages in mining.
40 mining [ISO 22739:2020] - activity, in some consensus mechanisms, that creates and validates blocks or validates ledger records.
Note: Participation in mining is often incentivized by block rewards and transaction fees.
41 node(s) [ISO 22739:2020] - <organization of data> elementary component from which a data structure is built.
node [ITU SG17] device or process that participates in a distributed ledger network.
Note: Nodes can store a complete or partial replica of the distributed ledger.
41.2 leaf node [ISO 22739:2020] - node that has no child nodes.
41.3 full node* [NISTIR] 
41.4 lightweight node* [NISTIR] 
41.5 publishing node* [NISTIR] 
42 nonce [ISO 22739:2020] - number or bit string used once in a set of cryptographic operations
Note: A nonce is often random or pseudo-random. It is commonly used to guard against replay attacks, where a message is captured and re-sent by a malicious actor. In some blockchain systems it is used to modulate mining during the generation of a new block and is stored in the block header.
43 off-chain [ISO 22739:2020] - related to a blockchain system, but located, performed, or run outside that blockchain system.
44 off-ledger [ISO 22739:2020] - related to a DLT system, but located, performed, or run outside that DLT system.
45 on-chain [ISO 22739:2020] - located, performed, or run inside a blockchain system.
46 on-ledger [ISO 22739:2020] - located, performed, or run inside a DLT system.
47 oracle (DLT oracle)* [ITU SG17] - service that supplies information to a distributed ledger using data from outside of a distributed ledger system.
